# GitHub Issues And PRs

Use GitHub for code-hosting coordination unless a project explicitly defines GitHub as the backlog source. Linear, Jira, Saga, and Memory Bank keep their own authority boundaries.

## Principles

- Derive repository data dynamically; do not hardcode owner, repo, branch, or base branch.
- Deduplicate before creating issues or PRs.
- Use body files with `-F`/`--body-file` for newline-safe formatting.
- Assign intentionally and apply labels only when they are meaningful for the repository.
- Do not create or update Saga or Memory Bank entries from this rule unless the current task already requires those systems.

## Prerequisites

```sh
gh auth status
SLUG=$(gh repo view --json nameWithOwner -q .nameWithOwner)
BASE=$(gh repo view --json defaultBranchRef -q .defaultBranchRef.name)
```

If `gh` has no default repo and errors, set the derived repo explicitly:

```sh
gh repo set-default "$SLUG"
```

## Issue Creation

Search before creating:

```sh
EXISTING=$(gh issue list --repo "$SLUG" --search "in:title \"$TITLE\"" --json number,title,url -q '.[0].url' 2>/dev/null || true)
if [ -n "$EXISTING" ]; then
  printf 'Issue exists: %s\n' "$EXISTING"
  exit 0
fi
```

Create with a body file:

```sh
BODY_FILE=$(mktemp)
cat > "$BODY_FILE" <<'EOF'
Context:
- <why this issue exists>

Acceptance criteria:
- <testable outcome>
EOF

gh issue create --repo "$SLUG" --title "$TITLE" -F "$BODY_FILE" --assignee "@me"
```

## PR Creation

Prefer deduplicating by branch/head before title:

```sh
BRANCH=$(git branch --show-current)
if [ -z "$BRANCH" ]; then
  echo "No git branch detected; inspect jj bookmark or detached state before creating a PR" >&2
  exit 1
fi
EXISTING_PR=$(gh pr list --repo "$SLUG" --head "$BRANCH" --state open --json url -q '.[0].url' 2>/dev/null || true)
if [ -n "$EXISTING_PR" ]; then
  printf 'PR exists: %s\n' "$EXISTING_PR"
  exit 0
fi
```

Create with a body file:

```sh
PR_BODY_FILE=$(mktemp)
cat > "$PR_BODY_FILE" <<'EOF'
## Summary

- <what changed>
- <why>

## Validation

- <commands and PASS/FAIL status>

## Risks

- <known limitations or none>
EOF

gh pr create --repo "$SLUG" --base "$BASE" --head "$BRANCH" --title "$PR_TITLE" -F "$PR_BODY_FILE" --assignee "@me"
```

## Verification

- Confirm the created or reused issue/PR URL.
- Confirm labels, assignees, base branch, and body formatting.
- For PRs, confirm validation commands/results are present in the body.
- If an issue/PR duplicates an existing one, close or reuse it rather than creating another.
